{"action": "input", "code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    rows_index = find_non_black_rows(input_grid)\n    mod_rows_index = rows_index[:-1]\n    output_grid = input_grid\n    output_grid[mod_rows_index, 1:] = input_grid[mod_rows_index, :-1]\n    output_grid = copy_right_column_to_output_grid(input_grid, output_grid)\n    return output_grid\ndef find_non_black_rows(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in a numpy array as input and returns a list of row indices that contain any value other than black.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array of shape (n, m) where n is the number of rows and m is the number of columns.\n\n    Returns:\n    A list of row indices that contain any value other than black.\n    \"\"\"\n    non_black_rows = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        if not np.all(input_grid[i] == black):\n            non_black_rows.append(i)\n    return non_black_rows\ndef copy_right_column_to_output_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray, output_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        if input_grid[i, -1] != black:\n            output_grid[i, -1] = input_grid[i, -1]\n    return output_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n   rows_index = `find the rows that contain grid other than black and output the number list`(input_grid)\n   mod_rows_index = rows_index[:-1]\n   output_grid = input_grid\n   output_grid[mod_rows_index, 1:] = input_grid[mod_rows_index, :-1]\n   output_grid = `for each grid of rightmost column of the input_gird, if the color is not black, change the color of the grid with the same location in the output_grid to this color`(input_grid, output_grid)\n   return output_grid\n", "gpt_code": "def find_non_black_rows(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in a numpy array as input and returns a list of row indices that contain any value other than black.\n\n    Args:\n   